arge\nnumber of complex communities. The communities identified at the 10\\% threshold\nwere generally associated with common misconceptions producing a far richer set\nof incorrect communities than the FCI; this may indicate that the FMCE is a\nsuperior instrument for characterizing the breadth of student misconceptions\nabout Newtonian mechanics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Jan 2020 20:12:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-29"}
